# Snapshot & Freshness

Default behavior:
- Use active/latest snapshot unless user pins one.
- `pages.list` may auto-fallback to a fuller same-project snapshot when requested snapshot is incomplete.

Controls:
- `strictSnapshot:true` disables cross-snapshot fallback.
- `includeDeleted:true` includes soft-deleted pages.
- `snapshots.refresh` supports `fetchStrategy: auto|bulk|file`.
- `snapshots.refresh` uses chunked full file mode by default for `mode:"full", fetchStrategy:"file"` (reuses one list call across chunk passes).

When data looks wrong or stale:
1) Run `snapshots.info` and inspect `refreshedAt` and counts.
2) Run `pages.list` without strict mode to catch fallback warnings.
3) Run `snapshots.refresh` with conservative pacing.
4) Re-check `snapshots.info`.

Recommended refresh defaults under throttling:
- Incremental: `mode:"incremental", fetchStrategy:"auto", maxFetch:25, concurrency:1, sleepMs:250`
- Severe 429: `mode:"incremental", fetchStrategy:"file", maxFetch:5, concurrency:1, sleepMs:1000`
- Full sync attempt: `mode:"full", fetchStrategy:"bulk"`
- Chunked full fallback: `mode:"full", fetchStrategy:"file", maxFetch:5`

Authoritative state:
- Treat snapshot as authoritative only when full refresh reports `authoritative:true` and `pruneApplied:true`.

Do not conclude deletions from partial refreshes or 429-heavy runs.
